African leaders, businesses and brands are in for fresh positioning opportunities and top of mind awareness at the 2019 edition of African Business Excellence and Leadership Awards (ABELA) & Conference. 
   
The one day conference and award, put together by Hexagon Development Company Ltd., in conjunction with World Trade Organization (WTO), has as theme, Strategic Options for Business Transformations and Emerging Technologies. The event holds on August 30, at Rock View Hotel, Abuja.
     
Speaking at a media briefing in Lagos on the conference, Chairman, Awards  Committee, Dr. Bobby Martins, said the conference was specially packaged to focus on strategies, resolutions and way forward to promote businesses within Africa and in the international community. He also announced that it will reward exemplary leadership, innovation and excellence in businesses and leadership.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .